 2025 Paper Summaries and Analysis","href":"/blog/2025/04/25/eurosys-2025-paper-summaries-and-analysis/","depth":0},{"title":"GPU Profiling Under the Hood: An Implementation-Focused Survey of Modern Accelerator Tracing Tools","href":"/blog/2025/04/21/gpu-profiling-under-the-hood-an-implementation-focused-survey-of-modern-accelerator-tracing-tools/","depth":0},{"title":"The Accelerator Toolkit: A Review of Profiling and Tracing for GPUs and other co-processor","href":"/blog/2025/04/11/the-accelerator-toolkit-a-review-of-profiling-and-tracing-for-gpus-and-other-co-processor/","depth":0},{"title":"OS-Level Challenges in LLM Inference and Optimizations","href":"/blog/2025/02/18/os-level-challenges-in-llm-inference-and-optimizations/","depth":0},{"title":"WASI and the WebAssembly Component Model: Current Status","href":"/blog/2025/02/16/wasi-and-the-webassembly-component-model-current-status/","depth":0},{"title":"eBPF Ecosystem Progress in 2024–2025: A Technical Deep Dive","href":"/blog/2025/02/12/ebpf-ecosystem-progress-in-2024-2025-a-technical-deep-dive/","depth":0},{"title":"Security Vulnerabilities Study in Software Extensions and Plugins","href":"/blog/2025/02/10/security-vulnerabilities-study-in-software-extensions-and-plugins/","depth":0},{"title":"Can LLMs understand Linux kernel? A New AI-Powered Approach to Understanding Large Codebases","href":"/blog/2024/10/01/can-llms-understand-linux-kernel-a-new-ai-powered-approach-to-understanding-large-codebases/","depth":0},{"title":"Building High-Performance Userspace eBPF VMs with LLVM","href":"/blog/2024/09/10/building-high-performance-userspace-ebpf-vms-with-llvm/","depth":0},{"title":"The Past, Present, and Future of eBPF and Its Path to Revolutionizing Systems","href":"/blog/2024/08/11/the-past-present-and-future-of-ebpf-and-its-path-to-revolutionizing-systems/","depth":0},{"title":"Simplifying Kernel Programming: The LLM-Powered eBPF Tool","href":"/blog/2024/07/11/simplifying-kernel-programming-the-llm-powered-e